eType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Soft-boiled eggs","Raw seafood","Unpasteurised dairy products","P\u00e2t\u00e9","Bread"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EDuring pregnancy, \u003Cstrong\u003Ebread\u003C/strong\u003E is a safe and recommended food. In Australia, bread is fortified with folic acid which helps prevent neural tube defects. It is also a good source of energy and nutrients.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe following foods should be avoided during pregnancy due to infection risks:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESoft-boiled eggs\u003C/strong\u003E can contain salmonella bacteria\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ERaw seafood\u003C/strong\u003E carries risk of listeria and other food-borne pathogens\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EUnpasteurised dairy products\u003C/strong\u003E may contain listeria bacteria\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EP\u00e2t\u00e9\u003C/strong\u003E can harbour listeria and contains high levels of vitamin A which may be harmful to the developing fetus\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAdditional foods to avoid include raw or undercooked meat, pre-prepared salads, and soft cheeses due to infection risks. All fruits and vegetables should be thoroughly washed before consumption.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Folate supplementation is essential during pregnancy to prevent neural tube defects.","Bread in Australia is fortified with folic acid to help prevent neural tube defects.","Pregnant women should avoid foods that carry risk of toxoplasmosis, listeriosis, or salmonella infection."],"references":["Mackerras D, Powers J, Boorman J, Loxton D, Giles GG. Estimating the impact of mandatory fortification of bread with iodine on pregnant and post-partum women. J Epidemiol Community Health. 2011 Dec;65(12):1118-22. doi: 10.1136/jech.2009.089169. Epub 2010 Aug 13. PMID: 20709857.","Teixeira JA, Castro TG, Wall CR, Marchioni DM, Berry S, Morton SM, Grant CC. Effects of folic acid food fortification scenarios on the folate intake of a multi-ethnic pregnant population. Public Health Nutr. 2019 Mar;22(4):738-749. doi: 10.1017/S1368980018003026. Epub 2018 Dec 6. PMID: 30518437; PMCID: PMC10260456.","Thurston L, Borman B, Bower C. Mandatory fortification with folic acid for the prevention of neural tube defects: a case study of Australia and New Zealand. Childs Nerv Syst. 2023 Jul;39(7):1737-1741. doi: 10.1007/s00381-022-05823-x. Epub 2023 Jan 19. PMID: 36653503; PMCID: PMC10290585."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"49567"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16160"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"49567","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/49567"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-11-22T23:37:17+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-11-22T23:37:46+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8851"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"64135"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"23","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/23"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udd30","name":"Obstetrics","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"3"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"38","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/38"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83c\udf0f","name":"Public Health","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"6"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"6